export const hrHtml = "<p><em><u>SOCINGA AFRICA BUSINESS COMPANY</u></em></p>\n<p>HUMAN RESOURCES POLICY</p>\n<p>We Commit to Investors – Clients – Employees – Customers – Consumers\n– Visitors and every person interacting with us that we as the Board,\nSenior Executing Management and founders we shall observe the contents\nof this policy found by us at all times.</p>\n<p>Company Seal</p>\n<p><strong>Managing Directors Signature:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Oath Stamp and Signature</strong></p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>PURPOSE OF THE POLICY</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p><strong>To give effect</strong> to Socinga Structural Policy\nNo<strong>.</strong> 02/0000/2026</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>To outline</strong> personnel management measures,\ncontrols and policies for Socinga Africa</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>To display</strong> Recruitment and Selection systems for\neffective and efficient servi+ces to clients, consumers,\nemployees.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>To adhere</strong> to the international standards on\nmaintenance of human resources well being</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>To outlay</strong> transparent measures to Investors on\nthe type of personnel systems and employment processes in the\nbusiness</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>INTRODUCTIONS</strong></p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Socinga Africa desires to be a duly business constituted juristic\nbody in terms of the laws of the Republic of South Africa.</p></li>\n<li><p>Compliant to King V Code the business will establish its\nactivities directed by mainly its written rules, written norms, written\nstandards, written policies all aimed at ensuring it conducts all its\nbusiness separate from its founding owners.</p></li>\n<li><p>This policy will be applied in conjunction with Socinga Africa\nEstablishment policy, board of directors and senior executive management\ndecisions from time to time</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n<li><p><strong>PROVISIONS OF THE POLICY</strong></p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>This policy handles the regulation of worker control and\nbenefit</p></li>\n<li><p>This policy set forth issues of employment stages as related\nmanagement</p></li>\n<li><p>This policy articulates benefits</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n<li><p><strong>MANDATE OF THE HUMAN RESOURCES</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The mandate of this policy is to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Develop Human Resources Policies</p></li>\n<li><p>Give Advice</p></li>\n<li><p>Develop Personnel skills</p></li>\n<li><p>Enforce Discipline</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"5\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>LEGAL PROVISIONS</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<table>\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 52%\" />\n<col style=\"width: 47%\" />\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"header\">\n<th><strong>NAME OF LEGISLATION</strong></th>\n<th><strong>REFERENCE</strong></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Constitution of the Republic of South Africa</td>\n<td>Constitution, 1996</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td>Labour Relations Act</td>\n<td>Act No, 66 of 1995</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Basic Conditions of Employment Act</td>\n<td>Act No.75 of 1997</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td>Employment Equity Act</td>\n<td>Act No. 55 of 1998</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Unemployment Insurance Act</td>\n<td>Act No. 63 of 2001</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td>Compensation for Occupational Diseases Act</td>\n<td>Act No. 130 of 1993</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Occupational Health and Safety Act</td>\n<td>Act No. 85 of 1983</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td>Financial sector Regulation Act</td>\n<td>Act No. of 2017</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Long Term Insurance Act</td>\n<td>Act No. 52 of 1998</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>KEY REFERENCES</strong></p>\n<table>\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 51%\" />\n<col style=\"width: 48%\" />\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"header\">\n<th colspan=\"2\"><strong>INTERNAL DIRECTIVES</strong></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Organisational Code of Conduct</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td>Socinga Structural Policy</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Board Directives</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td>Occupational Health and Safety Policy</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Financial Sector conduct Authority</td>\n<td>Issued by the Prudent body</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ol start=\"6\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>STAGES OF EMPLOYMENT</strong></p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>It is important for the business to document its human resources\nmanagement and clearly display its personnel compliant to Policies and\nFramework.</p></li>\n<li><p>We recognise a need for a fair approach in handling the due\nnatural stages of employment within this company for healthy working\nstaff capable of performing to maximum capabilities</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"A\">\n<li><p><strong>Pre – Employment Stage</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong><u>Promoting Socinga as company of\nchoice</u></strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>It must be organised house of pride so much the People of the world\nand of quality service must dream to provide their valuable skill to it,\nthus take care of the following:</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p><u>Proper Branding is solidified by the actions the business\ntowards the society</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Even if not correct the customers the customer is always\nright</p></li>\n<li><p>Efforts must be made to take time to listen to the customers\nneeds with perseverance all the time</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p><u>Full image is promoted by the behavioural conduct of its\nworkers towards clients</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Respect the client addressing them with politeness at all costs\neven if shouting at you, never raise your voice.</p></li>\n<li><p>When customer or client not happy must be immediately referred to\nthe Supervisor for assistance</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"3\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p><u>Believe in company image is maintained by quality of company\nservice or product to consumers</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Provide services exactly as you promised, not subservient works\nnot lesser quality at any time</p></li>\n<li><p>Provide clients a chance to comment on service delivered and ask\nfor their suggestion for better service improvement</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"4\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p><u>Reliance of trust in company image can only be sustained by\nconduct of company executive leadership</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Have an open line for customers and clients to know can have\ntheir views about business listened to by top executive all the\ntime.</p></li>\n<li><p>The executive must be presentable in appearance and dress code\nall the time when in public eye</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"5\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p><u>Improvement in technological service and products offering can\ncapture the image</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Products offered must evolve with digital revolution and\ntechnicians be ahead in technology</p></li>\n<li><p>The services must be maintained paperless as possible</p></li>\n<li><p>Research, data collection and training must be maintained all the\ntime</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"6\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p><u>Incentives and remuneration as attractive pillar</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Staff must be encouraged to be innovative, perform better all the\ntime with incentive package</p></li>\n<li><p>Staff must be given good quality market and industry related\npayment packages and benefits</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Clear Display of Socinga Employment\nPolicies</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Employment policies belong to the investor, clients, employees,\nconsumers, personnel and the executive to have full understanding of the\nbusiness in order to make profits therefore handled transparently with\ncare as follows:</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Transparent recruitment and selection policy\ndirectives</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Advertisement of available work positions when vacancy\nemerges</p></li>\n<li><p>Disclose employment demographics of the staff in the company\nwebsite</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Job placements</u></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Appoint persons compliant to procedure published or made know\nupon vacancy advertisement</p></li>\n<li><p>If the appointment is not through open vacancy publishing process\nmust be through tangible approved procedure by the board</p></li>\n<li><p>Employ qualified persons who meets the job requirements strictly\nand who can add value and profit making to business</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Insurance Division</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The Managing Director, Director Corporate Services and Insurance line\nshall give effect to employment of relevant staff required for optimum\nprofitable service.</p>\n<p>The recruitment and selection policy and directives will be respected\nand adhered to.</p>\n<p>Recruitment must be in line with the essential requirements of the\ntask and terms of the industry</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Mining Division</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The Managing Director, CEO, head of corporate services, Cairperson\nand line shall give effect to employment of relevant staff required for\noptimum profitable service.</p>\n<p>The recruitment and selection policy and directives will be respected\nand adhered to.</p>\n<p>Recruitment must be in line with the essential requirements of the\ntask and terms of the industry</p>\n<p>Subject to specific recruitment and selection policy, this service\nmaybe outsourced as strategic norms and standards for optimal profit\nmaking.</p>\n<ol start=\"3\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Creative Studios</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The Managing Director, CEO and line shall give effect to employment\nof relevant staff required for optimum profitable service.</p>\n<p>The recruitment and selection policy and directives will be respected\nand adhered to.</p>\n<p>Recruitment must be in line with the essential requirements of the\ntask and terms of the industry</p>\n<ol start=\"4\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Foundation Division</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The Managing Director, CEO, Chair and line shall give effect to\nemployment of relevant staff required for optimum profitable\nservice.</p>\n<p>The recruitment and selection policy and directives will be respected\nand adhered to.</p>\n<p>Recruitment must be in line with the essential requirements of the\ntask and terms of the industry</p>\n<ol start=\"5\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Employment Safety Pre employment\nScreening</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Screening of applicants is essential for safety of clients,\nemployees, investor interest, consumers, staff and personnel and must be\ntaken seriously all the time before appointment of any person the\nfollowing must be carried out:</p>\n<p><strong>A prescribed form collecting applicants’ data is made\navailable on company website</strong></p>\n<ol start=\"6\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Basic Screening</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Short listing of applicants matching their qualifications against\nadvert requirements confirming their details:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>on Home Affairs,</p></li>\n<li><p>SAPS,</p></li>\n<li><p>Foreign Affairs,</p></li>\n<li><p>SAQA,</p></li>\n<li><p>Interpol,</p></li>\n<li><p>Credit check</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Mid employment Screening</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Request for personal finger print submission to office by applicant\nto meet with line and observe compatibility in appearance</p>\n<p>Physical Test on claim <strong>Eg</strong> <em>Psychometric\ntest</em></p>\n<p>Occupational Health Practitioner Medical test where required</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Final Screening Employment Screening</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Interviewing an applicant to test their skills, capabilities,\nknowledge, experience and capacity to be able to perform the work\nprofitably</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Confidential further screening check with previous 02 (two)\nemployers’ reference</p></li>\n<li><p>If doubt picked up on inconsistent submission conduct background\ncheck</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"A\">\n<li><p><strong>Post -Employment Stage</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Confirmation of appointment</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Check of budget is confirmed ad available to bear all payments on\nsalary and wages</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>CFO must issue credence through signature confirming money is\navailable by attaching budget print out</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Check if correct type of contract is prepared and\navailable</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>CEO or line must ensure there is a written clear contract for the\nappointee to sign</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"3\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Check if the induction date is prepared and the induction team is\nready</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>CEO or line must ensure the induction date is properly planned\nfor the new appointee</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"4\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Check if there are working teams to receive the appointee until\ncomfortable to can be on services</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>CEO must organise a team to receive the appointee to work with if\navailable</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"5\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Check tools and required equipment for the appointee if is in\nplace for issuing and control</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>CEO must ensure line has prepared tools required for new\nappointee to perform optimally</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Validating the appointment of a new\nemployee</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Appointment letter of a person for work is legally binding once the\ncontracting party receive it and acknowledged receipt of employment and\ntherefore must be carefully processed as it bears legal Quencequences,\ntherefore:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Only the office of the CEO can confirm the appointment of a new\nappointee</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Communicating confirmation of appointment</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>The office of the Director corporate services is in charge of\ncommunications.</p></li>\n<li><p>The CEO may communicate directly with the appointee and alert the\noffice of the Director Corporate services to have done so.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p>On boarding the new employee on the company system</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>No employee shall be on boarded until reported for duty and\nstarted to perform duties</p></li>\n<li><p>The Director Corporate services has the mandate to on board the\nnew appointees for legibility for payments and benefits.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"3\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Contractual work Appointments</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>3.1 The contracts in Socinga Africa may differ from division to\ndivision due to nature of work, field, practice and discipline</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Contract can be for temporary work or permanent nature of\nemployment</p></li>\n<li><p>Contracts can be for special condition in Memorandum Agreement\n[<strong>MOA</strong>]</p></li>\n<li><p>Agreements in Memorandum of Understanding [<strong>MOU</strong>]\nare not recognised in and for purpose of this Policy</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>This policy is for personnel appointed as employees who are under\ndirect supervision, appointments, paid salary in cash or in kind per\nstipulations expressed in clear written forms of appointment.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Insurance Division</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ul>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p><u>Insurance services is controlled by regulations of the\nFinancial Sector Conduct Authority and its council</u></p></li>\n<li><p>The employment contracts for all functionaries in the executive\nwill include binding reference to the requirements of the Act</p></li>\n<li><p>The employment contracts for the management and employees\nappointed for the service will reflect conduct for the industry</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Type of Contracts</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Type of employment contracts will be informed by the nature of\nneeds and operational requirement considering highest Profit making\npossible as first priority;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Term contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract of employment for specific time only and which maybe for\nany operational requirements</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Project based contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>A contract specifically for a period of a defined project\nwork;</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>time is not main measurement but specific works,</p></li>\n<li><p>budget availability and</p></li>\n<li><p>certified end of works</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Standard contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ul>\n<p>A contract specifically designed for an unending period due to nature\nof business operational requirements almost like a permanent employment\nintent if;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The intention is to employ or enter into possible permanent\nemployment contract for a long time</p></li>\n<li><p>Remunerate benefits differently from other contracts</p></li>\n<li><p>Allocate legal agreement terms and conditions of employment to a\nsimilar group</p></li>\n<li><p>A group of employees entitled to be appointed with a business\ngoing concern</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Specialist contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract for a nature of scarce skills performance in which the\nspecial terms of agreement are to recognise the following;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Specialist terms and conditions of employment</p></li>\n<li><p>Specialist working apparatuses</p></li>\n<li><p>Special form of remuneration within other groups</p></li>\n<li><p>Requirements for retainer of significant employees to the\ncompany</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Mining Division</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p><u>Mining services is controlled by regulations of the statutory\nMining Acts and the related bargaining councils</u></p></li>\n<li><p>The employment contracts for all functionaries in the executive\nwill include binding reference to the requirements of the Act</p></li>\n<li><p>The employment contracts for the management and employees\nappointed for the service will reflect conduct for the industry</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Type of Contracts</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Type of employment contracts will be informed by the nature of needs\nand operational requirement considering highest Profit making possible\nas first priority;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Term contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract of employment for specific time only and which maybe for\nany operational requirements</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Project based contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>A contract specifically for a period of a defined project\nwork;</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><p>time is not main measurement but specific works,</p></li>\n<li><p>budget availability and</p></li>\n<li><p>certified end of works</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Standard contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ul>\n<p>A contract specifically designed for an unending period due to nature\nof business operational requirements almost like a permanent employment\nintent if;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The intention is to employ or enter into possible permanent\nemployment contract for a long time</p></li>\n<li><p>Remunerate benefits differently from other contracts</p></li>\n<li><p>Allocate legal agreement terms and conditions of employment to a\nsimilar group</p></li>\n<li><p>A group of employees entitled to be appointed with a business\ngoing concern</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Specialist contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract for a nature of scarce skills performance in which the\nspecial terms of agreement are to recognise the following;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Specialist terms and conditions of employment</p></li>\n<li><p>Specialist working apparatuses</p></li>\n<li><p>Special form of remuneration within other groups</p></li>\n<li><p>Requirements for retainer of significant employees to the company\nto give effect to Socinga Strategic Policy No. 04/0000/2026</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Creative studios media and Broadcasting</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p><u>Creative Arts, Media and Broadcasting is mainly controlled by\nregulations of the Films Act and Broadcasting corporation Act</u></p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The employment contracts for all functionaries in the executive\nwill include binding reference to the requirements of the Act</p></li>\n<li><p>The employment contracts for the management and employees\nappointed for the service will reflect conduct for the industry</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Type of Contracts</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Type of employment contracts will be informed by the nature of needs\nand operational requirement considering highest Profit making possible\nas first priority;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Term contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract of employment for specific time only and which maybe for\nany operational requiements</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Project based contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract specifically for a period of a defined project work;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>time is not main measurement but specific works,</p></li>\n<li><p>budget availability and</p></li>\n<li><p>certified end of works</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Standard contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract specifically designed for an unending period due to nature\nof business operational requirements almost like a permanent employment\nintent if;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The intention is to employ or enter into possible permanent\nemployment contract for a long time</p></li>\n<li><p>Remunerate benefits differently from other contracts</p></li>\n<li><p>Allocate legal agreement terms and conditions of employment to a\nsimilar group</p></li>\n<li><p>A group of employees entitled to be appointed with a business\ngoing concern</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Specialist contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract for a nature of scarce skills performance in which the\nspecial terms of agreement are to recognise the following;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Specialist terms and conditions of employment or</p></li>\n<li><p>Memorandum of Understanding [MOU] is concluded to give effect to\nprovisions of Policy No. 01/0000/2026</p></li>\n<li><p>Specialist working apparatuses</p></li>\n<li><p>Special form of remuneration within other groups</p></li>\n<li><p>Requirements for retainer of significant employees to the\ncompany</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Foundation Corporate Social Investment</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p><u>Foundation services is controlled by regulations of the statutory\nprovisions in the Consumer Protection Act</u></p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The employment contracts for all functionaries in the executive\nwill include binding reference to the requirements of the Act</p></li>\n<li><p>The employment contracts for the management and employees\nappointed for the service will reflect conduct for the industry</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Type of Contracts</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Type of employment contracts will be informed by the nature of needs\nand operational requirement considering highest Profit making possible\nas first priority;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Term contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract of employment for specific time only and which maybe for\nany operational requirents</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Project based contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract specifically for a period of a defined project work;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>time is not main measurement but specific works,</p></li>\n<li><p>budget availability and</p></li>\n<li><p>certified end of works</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Standard contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract specifically designed for an unending period due to nature\nof business operational requirements almost like a permanent employment\nintent if;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The intention is to employ or enter into possible permanent\nemployment contract for a long time</p></li>\n<li><p>Remunerate benefits differently from other contracts</p></li>\n<li><p>Allocate legal agreement terms and conditions of employment to a\nsimilar group</p></li>\n<li><p>A group of employees entitled to be appointed with a business\ngoing concern</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Specialist contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>A contract for a nature of scarce skills performance in which the\nspecial terms of agreement are to recognise the following;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Specialist terms and conditions of employment</p></li>\n<li><p>Specialist working apparatuses</p></li>\n<li><p>Special form of remuneration within other groups</p></li>\n<li><p>Requirements for retainer of significant employees to the company\nto give effect to Socinga Strategic Policy No. 04/0000/2026</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>The Executive Authority</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The executing authority is the highest decision making body\ncomprised of the Executive board and its chairperson.</p></li>\n<li><p>The functions of the board and its mandate are deriving its\nexistence and powers from the Socinga Africa establishment\npolicy</p></li>\n<li><p>The board is supreme governance structure as a business body per\nthe constitution of the republic of South Africa 1996 and subsequent\nbusiness operations arrangements with Socinga Mgabadeli Pty Ltd\npermitting it to trade as per its independent juristic mandate</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Type of contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The type of contracts with the board members maybe concluded per\ndirectives in recognisable legal instruments in Socinga Africa\nEstablishment policy 01/0000/2026</p></li>\n<li><p>Agreement for services with members of the board maybe concluded\nper Memorandum of Agreement [MOU] entered into with the managing\nDirector of Socinga Africa being Ms Jabulile Dladla</p></li>\n<li><p>Further an ordinary contractual binding legal employment\nagreement maybe entered into and concluded to appoint members of the\nboard on clear specific terms and conditions.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Term contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>A contract of employment for specific time only and which maybe\nfor any operational requirements</p></li>\n<li><p>The contractual agreement may be perpetual in nature due to a\nspecified Socinga Africa hand book for Board members to be issued on the\napproval of the board itself</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>The External functionaries</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>These are experienced persons of enormous exposure in business to\nassist with external relations insisting on brokerage of perfect image\non services bench marked on lack of such personnel in the immediate\ncontractual employment.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Type of contract</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Head hunting concluded in a service level agreement utilising a\nMemorandum of Understanding.</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>These functionaries may be serving in other institutions or\nowning some institutions accepted by the board</p></li>\n<li><p>The persons so entered into agreement with draws no salary other\nthan a commission on the project based agreement and term</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Performance Management Development\nSystems</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>It is important to appoint the staff and personnel that have terms\nand conditions of service able to be measured with the scientific\nprofessional system that is open, fair, and transparent in goals and\nobjectives of activities</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong><u>Measuring work performance</u></strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The performance management development system will be expressed\nin a written form where Duties are measured against each activity of a\nKey performance Area that follows the work objectives measured on time\nand indicators so as remuneration of salaries are not in vain.</p></li>\n<li><p>Therefore the policy must be borne from Key Performance\nIndicators within the structure as baseline of Key performance area in a\n<u><strong>S</strong>imple</u> <u><strong>M</strong>easurable</u>\n<u><strong>A</strong>chievable</u> <u><strong>R</strong>eliable</u>\n<u><strong>T</strong>ransparent</u> form</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong><u>Effect of performance\nmeasurement</u></strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The performance management system will drive profitability and\nnecessity to remunerate fairly or penalise the affected employee or\nstaff members in the following areas;</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Promotions</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Promotions will come with incentive within either of the\noccurrence following:</p></li>\n<li><p>A vacancy exists and there is a need to appoint a person into\nthat vacancy which could results in higher position or better income\nfrom the currently occupied post</p></li>\n<li><p>A company decides to promote persons who are in a dedicated\nemployment for a lengthy period of over five years in the same position\nif can afford to carry them reliably for at least another coming five\nyears period with benefits consistently.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Working Time</strong></p></li>\n<li><p><u>Personnel and employees respecting a working time\nby</u></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Respecting the work time at all times</p></li>\n<li><p>Not misusing the employment time in an errand manner</p></li>\n<li><p>Conducting themselves in a manner that do not inconveniences or\ndisrupts the working arrangements of the company towards clients,\nconsumers, customers, visitors,</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Training</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Attend to committed training internally and learn the new or\nmaintenance of acquired skill</p></li>\n<li><p>Take training seriously to upgrade their skill</p></li>\n<li><p>Employees able to measure poor or good performance that require\ntraining intervention</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Regular assessments</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p><u>At least 4 times a year a supervisory assessment of the employees\ncan take place</u></p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>To ensure there is quality provision of services</p></li>\n<li><p>To ensure there is betterment on performance</p></li>\n<li><p>To ensure there is betterment of staff and employees personal\ngrowth</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Remuneration</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Payments of benefits encourages performance and dedication to\nwork at times even devoted personnel to the company so much they become\na promotion of good image to the entre outside world.</p></li>\n<li><p>The salaries should be structured in a manner compatible to each\nindustry requirements and practices in relation to computation of\nsalary</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Salary day</u></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The salary day can be per completion of task or per day or per\nweek or per fortnight or per month</p></li>\n<li><p>The pay day dates will be determined by the type of\nindustry</p></li>\n<li><p>The directives on salary structures will be raised by the CEO an\ntable to the board for approval</p></li>\n<li><p>The salaries must be industry competitive as, seek to assist in\nstaff retainer and drive the image of Socinga Africa as employee of\nchoice</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Incentives</u></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Over above ordinary pay day salary, incentive pay in a form of\ncommission is allowed to employees performing over above\nordinary.</p></li>\n<li><p>This incentive will be structured by the CEO and approved by the\nManaging director after consultation with the board</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Insurance Division</strong></p></li>\n<li><p>Salaries</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Carried out per the conduct of the insurance industry</p></li>\n<li><p>Reflection of payment will follow on recorded employment\ncontract</p></li>\n<li><p>Some work appointment may be verbal especially on marketing staff\nif approved by the Managing Director</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong><u>Incentives</u></strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Incentives can be an agreed commission; Or</p></li>\n<li><p>A special awarded performance bonus</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Mining Division</strong></p></li>\n<li><p>Salaries</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The salaries will follow international standard of payments and\nremuneration benefits in the industry.</p></li>\n<li><p>These payments of salaries may vary in nature of work and\ncontractual terms</p></li>\n<li><p>Profitability of the mining division should take precedence.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Incentives</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>CEO must find and develop some incentive structure which can be\nin a form of bonus payment</p></li>\n<li><p>The incentive scheme should be about rewarding excellence to team\nwork Eg. Achieving a safely working milieu without incidents [lets say\n1000000 working hours]</p></li>\n<li><p>The incentive scheme should take place if the company is\nprofitable in its works.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Creative studios media and Broadcasting</strong></p></li>\n<li><p>Salaries</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Salaries must follow the industry practices and\nstandards</p></li>\n<li><p>Media benefits must be carefully crafted on specific work\ncontracts for a specific role</p></li>\n<li><p>You may have two similar roles at different levels earning\ndifferently</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Incentives</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Incentives must be created as talent base performance measurement not\ngeneric</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Foundation</strong></p></li>\n<li><p>Salaries</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Benefits, wages and salaries should be structured to make success\nof project and company profitability</p></li>\n<li><p>Salaries must always be left open for negotiations and\nrenegotiations by the company</p></li>\n<li><p>The salary clause in the contractual agreement should reflect\nthis liquidity position otherwise this policy overrides any exclusion by\nintent or error in any employment contract.</p></li>\n<li><p>Incentives</p></li>\n<li><p>Incentives must be high enough to can invite and attract talent\nin ordinary hand crafts based works, Gardening designs and horticultural\nsculpting</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Discipline</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Discipline is an integral part of the working place and work\nfloor institution to achieve its maximum performance and profit making\nachievements.</p></li>\n<li><p>Discipline should not be a punitive measure but corrective in\nnature.</p></li>\n<li><p>Discipline process will be handled by Human Resources assisted by\nIndustrial relations in a principle of Employees relations norms than\njust industrial management</p></li>\n<li><p>Discipline seeks to deal with and handle behavioural misconduct\nof staff, employees in general, and personnel in general in a process of\nrecognised subordinates within the line on these areas;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Warnings</u></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>One of the basic and fundamental powers in the hands of the\ndisciplining authority being supervisory management is the issuing of\neither written or verbal warning to an employee who transgresses for the\nfirst time on an offence that may be carrying minor penalty.</p></li>\n<li><p>Repetitive minor offence and or rather serious offence may\nresults in issuing of written warning or final written warning</p></li>\n<li><p>All warnings including verbal warnings must be recorded on the\nfile of the employee after have been brought to his or her knowledge and\nsigned for its acknowledgement.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong><u>Demotion</u></strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>One of the basic and fundamental powers in the hands of the\ndisciplining authority being supervisory management is the issuance of\ndemotion as progressive discipline by recommending a disciplinary\nprocess with the outcome to demote the transgressor if the behavioural\nconduct is so adverse in that it has a potential to;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Tarnish the image of the business</p></li>\n<li><p>Results in a minor financial loss to a company</p></li>\n<li><p>The minor offence of warning procedural penalty will not befit\nractifying the behaviour</p></li>\n<li><p>The CEO shall receive the recommendation which the the Managing\nDirector can be the confirming authority after hearing the\nmatter.</p></li>\n<li><p>The chairperson of the board may become an appeal authority\nwithin 5 days of receiving the complaint</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong><u>Expulsion</u></strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>One of the basic measures important to progressive discipline against\nserious transgressions in the hands of senior management is Expilsion\nwhich may take the following form</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong><u>Suspension</u></strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The employee whose actions are of insubordination, violation of\nan established code of conduct, acts of crimes, acts of negligence, acts\nof violence, acts of defiance, acts related to theft and all acts listed\nor not in any form that can affect the company shall receive heavy\npunishment and no minor penalty other than the following</p></li>\n<li><p>Three months suspension without payment; Or</p></li>\n<li><p>Dismissal in a disciplinary process subject to post hearing;\nor</p></li>\n<li><p>Summary Dismissal applicable with immediate decision by the\nchairperson of the board</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Transfer as precaution</u></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Transfer of any employee can take place as a precautionary\nmeasure when the alleged transgression so serious may require\ninvestigations before allegations are confirmeg especially cases related\nto complaints of sexual harassment.</p></li>\n<li><p>In the event precautionary transfer is not possible due to\noperational requirements, the alleged transgressor may be sent to work\nfrom home with or without pay</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Disciplinary process</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>For discipline to be fair it must reflect the principle of\njustice in the workplace and this must be articulated in a written\nprocess to be known by everyone in the working environment including\ninvestors, employees, management, personnel, staff, visitors and any\ninterested person.</p></li>\n<li><p>The process must be outlined in the disciplinary code of\nconduct</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Disciplinary procedure</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>For discipline to be fair, the disciplinary procedure must have a\nclear procedure which ensures the principle of justice are achieved of\nwhich the minimum in this policy must 0penly display the\nfollowing;</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"i\">\n<li><p>Open hearing</p></li>\n<li><p>Independent chairperson</p></li>\n<li><p>Provision of adequate time to prepare for hearing</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Serving a charge sheet to alleged transgressor with clear reasons\nfor disciplinary charges, time and place of hearing (if any) and right\nto representation by a third party</p></li>\n<li><p>The right to have access to evidence and any records to be used\nagainst as evidence prior the hearing</p></li>\n<li><p>The procedure must be outlined in a disciplinary code or\npolicy</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>The code of conduct</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The code of conduct is an important document that can ensure that\ndiscipline is enforceable in a fair and just manner.</p></li>\n<li><p>The code of conduct will be drafted indicating minimum behaviours\nthat can be punishable, the procedure and the sanction.</p></li>\n<li><p>While the code of conduct not yet in place this policy will serve\nas a guide</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Breaking the Code</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Breaking the code of conduct is regarded a serious offence and shall\nbe punishable with adverse results.</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Transgressions inviting official discipline</strong></p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Charge Sheet</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>When any employee committed actions that call for official\ndiscipline shall mean any action which cannot be disciplines by evoking\na Warning.</p></li>\n<li><p>For this type of behavioural conduct a formal charge sheet must\nbe issued stating all the charges as alleged.</p></li>\n<li><p>No employee in this instance must be issued with sanctions\nwithout fair, just, open and proper hearing.</p></li>\n<li><ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Hearing</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Hearing must be conducted in a professional manner in which the\ncomplainant cannot be a player and the referee at the same time in that\nthe following role players must be present;</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The presiding officer</p></li>\n<li><p>The initiator</p></li>\n<li><p>The witnesses</p></li>\n<li><p>The accused</p></li>\n<li><p>The accused representatives of choice</p></li>\n<li><p>The witnesses from either side</p></li>\n<li><p>All seated and converged in the same room at the same process</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Outcome</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Disciplinary hearing shall be first communicated with the\naffected party being the employee especially when the results are\nadverse; notifying him or her in writing with proof of undoubtful\nreceipt then files it with the employees file notifying the chairperson\nof the board to have done so.</p></li>\n<li><p>This must be done within 5 working days</p></li>\n<li><p>The notice must inform the employee of his or her rights of\nappeal by notifying Managing Director within 48 hours and submitting the\nappeal documents with the chairperson within 10 working days</p></li>\n<li><p>This must be done within five working days</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Implementation of an outcome of hearing</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Upon the notification of the Managing Director about the outcome\nin the form of a sanction without receiving notification within of\nintent to appeal the sanction 48 hours of receipt, the sanction will be\ngiven effect.</p></li>\n<li><p>The time of compliance shall be observed strictly</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Appealing the decision of the hearing</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>The chairperson is the appeal authority and has the right to\nappoint any independent official as an appeal officer</p></li>\n<li><p>The appeal must be finalised within five days of receipt of\nappeal records and which results must be communicated in writing.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Finalisation of disciplinary outcome</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Finalisation of the appeal outcome will be by filing the entire\nrecord and save it in the office responsible for keeping the record at\nleast for five years</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Insurance Division</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Insurance division may be assisted by corporate services to\nconduct the disciplinary process</p></li>\n<li><p>The disciplinary outcome will be implemented by the Managing\nDirector or CEO</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Mining Division</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Mining division may be assisted by Employee relations to conduct\nthe disciplinary process</p></li>\n<li><p>Reason being that the industry is highly unionised with\ninterwoven various bargaining councils</p></li>\n<li><p>The disciplinary outcome will be implemented by CEO</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Creative studios media and Broadcasting</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Creative studios and Broadcasting division may be assisted by\ncorporate services to conduct the disciplinary process</p></li>\n<li><p>The disciplinary outcome will be implemented by the Head of\nStudios.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Foundation</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Foundation division may be assisted by corporate services to\nconduct the disciplinary process</p></li>\n<li><p>The Disciplinary Process will be implemented by the Managing\nDirector</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Legislation and Laws</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The legislation and laws of the country forms an integral part of our\ncompany and particularly Human Resources management Policies, Directives\nand Instructions, all divisions are expected to observe them in the\nfollowing manner;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Insurance Division</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Always take care of what is best compliance with the legislation\npertaining to its activities.</p></li>\n<li><p>Check what is in the best interest of the company</p></li>\n<li><p>Apply policies in conjunction with the law governing insurance\nindustry</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Mining Division</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Always take care of what is best compliance with the legislation\npertaining to its activities.</p></li>\n<li><p>Check what is in the best interest of the company</p></li>\n<li><p>Apply policies in conjunction with the law governing mining\nindustry</p></li>\n<li><p>Must do its best to liaise and obtain regular advice from\ncorporate services specialists</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Creative studios media and Broadcasting</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Always take care of what is best compliance with the legislation\npertaining to its activities.</p></li>\n<li><p>Check what is in the best interest of the company</p></li>\n<li><p>Apply policies in conjunction with the law governing creative\nstudios, media and broadcasting industry</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Foundation</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Always take care of what is best compliance with the legislation\npertaining to its activities.</p></li>\n<li><p>Check what is in the best interest of the company</p></li>\n<li><p>Apply policies in conjunction with the law governing foundation\nindustry</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>Classifications of level of Employment</strong></p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The following positions are exemplary of Socinga Africa Company\nhierarchy of Power;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Board of Directors</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Governs over entire corporate structure of Socinga Africa</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Executing Management</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Governs over specific division subject to control by Socinga Board of\nDirectors</p>\n<ol start=\"3\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Senior Management</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Manages specific divisional units subject to the directives from\nline</p>\n<ol start=\"4\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Junior Management</p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Supervisory personnel in the implementation stage of works\naccountable to junior management and or line</p>\n<ol start=\"5\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Support staff</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>All employees in the entry level of work in each division per type of\nwork irrespective of the significance on the employment level or\nposition</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><u>Training and development</u></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Training schedule must be made available planned properly for\neach performance period</p></li>\n<li><p>The plan must be in place to informing the budget</p></li>\n<li><p>Performance management system will identify and spot talent of\npersonnel thereby hugely influence training validation</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"3\" type=\"A\">\n<li><p><strong>Exit – Employment Stage</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>End of work relationship is common cause therefore inevitable\nhowever proper management is required for a company to remain healthy,\nkeep its clients, its consumers, its customers, its employees, its\nstaff, its personnel, its workers and its brand intact. This company\nmust ensure preparations in handling the following events;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Resignation</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>This is recognised stage on ending employment relationship and\nmust be initiated by the employee by issuing a written Notice</p></li>\n<li><p>Employees who issues a month long resignation notice time are\nencouraged and lose no benefits</p></li>\n<li><p>Employees who issues less a month notice and not less than 15\ndays accepted, may lose voluntary benefits and maybe employable back to\nthis company in the future</p></li>\n<li><p>Employees who issues seven working days period are welcomed but\nloses most benefits including end termination benefits</p></li>\n<li><p>Employees who issues less seven working days notice loses all\nbenefits</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Termination</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Termination of employment may come in two folds;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Abscondment</p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Where employee not reporting at work without permission, disappears,\nabandons work, not intending to come back to work after full 15 days of\nnot being reporting for duty</p>\n<p>Employee must have been issued with notice to come back to work but\nrefused to do so</p>\n<ol start=\"2\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Dessertion</p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>When the employee leaves work without permission, abandons duties\nwith intention not to return to work and not to come back.</p>\n<p>1.3 Dismissal</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>It is a termination of employment following Disciplinary process\nwithin the legitimate disciplinary process.</p></li>\n<li><p>When a person is dismissed, all his or her benefits due must be\nreleased within 48 hours but not later than seven working days</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Medical illness</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Medical illness or condition may lead to the End of work\nrelationship if;</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"i\">\n<li><p>It hinders the employee from exercising his or her work as\nexpected</p></li>\n<li><p>If there is no post to place the employee in another alternative\nwork function, the employee may be released with full benefits</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Death</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Death is an unfortunate event that terminates the employment\nrelationship in the journey of life and must be handled as follows;\nAnd</p></li>\n<li><p>After coming to know about the passing away of an employee the\nmatter must be brought to the attention of Director Corporate Services\nto:</p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"i\">\n<li><p>Officially confirm the information if it is true</p></li>\n<li><p>Inform the board immediately with circumstances around the\ndeceased information</p></li>\n<li><p>Liaise with the family and nominated beneficiaries if there are\nany</p></li>\n<li><p>Inform the company employees through the office of the Managing\nDirector</p></li>\n<li><p>Follow the Directives from the chairperson of the Board through\nthe board itself</p></li>\n<li><p>Benefits re not withheld in any manner except setting off debt\nthe employee had in moneys due to the company</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>End of contract</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>This happens by effluxion of time and no permanent employment\nexpectation should be created</p></li>\n<li><p>The contract must be managed effectively so as 15 days prior the\nexpiry of contract and before the contract ends all benefits due must\nhave been communicated with the personnel so affected.</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Retrenchment</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Retrenchment may become a real event where the company survival\nis left with no any other option than laying off the employees</p></li>\n<li><p>This must be handled with the approval of the board which must\nreceive a report with full clear reasons and proof of consultation\nprocess by and from the following offices;</p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>CEO</p></li>\n<li><p>Director corporate Services</p></li>\n<li><p>Managing Director</p></li>\n<li><p>Chief Financial Officer</p></li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"7\" type=\"1\">\n<li><p><strong>POLICY REVIEW</strong></p></li>\n</ol>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>This policy must be reviewed at least every 2 years by the board\ninitiated by the CEO assisted by Corporate services</p></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Duly Signed and Approved: Date:</p>\n<p>Managing Director CEO Chairperson</p>\n";
